    <p>
        <b>1. Shivaji Fort</b></p>
    <p>
     &nbsp;<img alt="" class="style19" 
            src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/dandali1.jpg" /></p>
     <p>An impeccable destination for heritage lovers and trek enthusiasts, another most desired tourist destination among the best things to do in Dandeli is the historic Shivaji Fort. It is believed to be once built by the Maratha Head, Chhatrapati Shivaji back in his times. The fort proudly boasts of the clever warring techniques and strategies implemented by the warriors to win an ongoing war and protect the fort from the enemies.

</p>
<p>Location: Haliyal Taluk, Uttara Kannada District, Karnataka
</p>
<p>Entry fees: None
</p>
<p>Places to stay: Whistling Woods, Jungle Lodges Kali Wilderness </p>
<p>Camp
Nearby Restaurants: Bison River Resort, Amara Homestay, Whistling Woodz</p>

 
       <p><b>2. Kavala Caves</b></p> 
       &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" class="style20" 
    src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/dandeli2.jpg" /><p>Get ready for some trek down 375 steps to see the age back Shivlinga formed by some volcanic activities in the exotic Kavala Caves. Visited by pilgrims from all over the country, especially on occasions like Shiv Ratri, Kavala Caves also welcome nature lovers and photography freaks to witness a phenomenal creation of nature. River Kali slowly enters the caves from 40 feet down. Kavala caves is a surreal yet important place on the list of places to visit in Dandeli for 1 day.

</p>
<p>Location: Kavala Caves, Lalguli, Karnataka 581363
</p>
<p>Entry fee: 10 rupees
</p>
<p>Places to stay: Magenta Resort Dandel
</p>
<p>Nearby Restaurants: Kamath Refreshment, Vali’s Hyderabadi Biryani Plaza</p>

   
    <p><b>3. Sathodi Falls</b></p> 
    <img alt="" class="style21" 
    src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/Dandeli3.jpg" />
    <p>Another one on our list of best places near Dandeli is Sathodi Falls. The fresh mountain air and the panoramic view of the water cascading from a great height make Sathodi Falls an ultimate destination for people who want to experience a peaceful and soulful getaway from the chaotic city life. The melancholy of the daily routines disappears on planning a one day picnic at the marvellous Sathodi falls. However, Sathodi falls becomes a salient attraction among the famous things to do in Dandeli and is one of the most serene waterfalls near Bangalore in Karnataka

</p>
<p>Location: Balagar, Karnataka
</p>
<p>Entry fee: 5 rupees </p>
<p>Places to stay: Small Hotel
Nearby Restaurants: Shanbhag Restaurant, Manjushri Hotels

</p>
<p>Tips: Beware of leeches and do carry food and water along</p>

   
    <p>4<b>. Syntheri Rocks</b></p> 
    <img alt="" class="style22" 
    src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/Dandeli4.jpg" />
    <p>Situated in close proximity to the Ulavi Temple, Syntheri Rocks becomes a must-visit for all the devotees who visit the temple at first. Syntheri Rocks is a granite structure attracting vacationers from all over the nation to witness this simply elegant home of numerous bird species, especially pigeons. Tourists places around Dandeli surely call for a halt at Syntheri Rocks to witness the giant magnificent rocks made of granite. One can easily reach the destination either by walking down about 200 steps from Ulavi Temple or hiring a jeep to the rocks.

</p>
<p>Location: Gund, Karnataka, 581186
</p>
<p>Entry fees:  INR 20 per person
</p>
<p>Places to stay: Dandeli Resorts
</p>
<p>Nearby Restaurants: Dandeli Kingfisher Stay</p>